org.archive.wayback.replay

Class DateRedirectingClosestResultSelector

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.archive.wayback.replay.DateRedirectingClosestResultSelector
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ClosestResultSelector
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ArchivalUrlDateRedirectingClosestResultSelector
    Deprecated. 
    1.8.1 2014-07-02 now this class is identical to DefaultClosestResultSelector in behavior.

    public class DateRedirectingClosestResultSelector
extends Object
implements ClosestResultSelector
    ClosestResultSelector that redirects to Archival-URL replay URL for the capture given if its timestamp is different from the request.

    This class is deprecated because 1) it does not preserve context flags upon redirect. 2) can cause redirect loop.
